ByteArrayList is a mechanism to ship array of byte arrays from Java to JNI in SQL part of Trafodion. It is found that the use of ByteArrayList class is expensive due to JNI to java transitions for every entry. In almost all cases the size of the byte array is known in advance and hence it would perform best if it is used as array of byte arrays. I have made changes already to avoid the use of ByteArrayList in Trafodion code base in all cases. However, I have retained the ByteArrayList JNI interface to ensure that the build is not broken when this change is merged to other feature branches.  After a short time if there are no objections, I will eliminate the ByteArrayList JNI interfaces entirely.

So, please if you can plan to use ByteArrayList in near future, you should defer your changes till this is done and consider using array of byte arrays instead.

Now, it works as this:
In code gen of HIVE_SCAN, if the CQD HIVE_SCAN_SPECIAL_MODE is set to '2'. Generate a CAST function setting a special flag. In that CAST codegen, it will set runtime flag based on the special flag. This will create a special ex_conv_clause.
Codegen also disable pCode in this mode.
At runtime, ex_conv_caluse::eval() will move null into target if convDoIt() failed. And continue.

The transaction object should get cleaned. In this case, for some reasons, either the transaction object is cleaned but not the scanner, or the transaction is aborted (not cleaned yet)  and the scanner is not. Current change is good enough since aborted trasnaction object should get cleaned. Under rare case, we might have a stale scanner with an aborted (but not cleaned) transaction object (likely a bug). In this situation, it's ok to move ahead by ignoring the stale scanner and aborted transaction object. Let us just use the current change.
